full_content.content: Common reasons your Magic Chef freezer is not cooling
The most common reasons your Magic Chef freezer is not cooling are a failed compressor, malfunctioning electronic control board or a bad evaporator.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
Magic Chef freezers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Magic Chef freezer

When your freezer is not cooling, a failed compressor could be causing the problem. The function of a freezer compressor is to compress and pump the refrigerant gas that flows through the sealed system, which in turns absorbs and removes heat from the inside of the freezer, keeping it cool. When the compressor fails, the freezer won’t cool at all. Because the EPA regulates the handling and disposal of all refrigerants, you’ll need to have a certified service technician perform the repair. Schedule service through Sears Home Services and we’ll send a certified technician to your home to fix your freezer.
How to replace a freezer compressor start relay

When your freezer is not cooling, a malfunctioning electronic control board could be causing the problem. The electronic control board receives signals from various sensors to monitor the temperature inside the freezer. Using the information it receives from these sensors, the board starts or stops the compressor, fans, defrost cycle and other components. A bad internal relay or corrupted internal logic on the circuit board can prevent the electronic control board from sending electric current to the compressor for cooling. When your freezer isn’t cooling, schedule service through Sears Home Services. Our technician will visit your home and fix the cooling problem in your freezer.
How to replace a freezer electronic control board

When your freezer is not cooling, a bad evaporator can be causing the problem. The evaporator cools the air inside the freezer. When the evaporator leaks all of the refrigerant out of the sealed system, the freezer won’t cool at all. Replacing the evaporator involves recovering and recharging the refrigerant in the sealed system. Because the EPA regulates the handling and disposal of all refrigerants, a certified service technician is required to perform the repair. When your freezer won’t cool at all, have a Sears Home Services Technician visit your home and fix the problem.

full_content.content: Power supply issues are a leading cause of your Magic Chef freezer not working. If your freezer has an interior light, open the door to see if the light turns on. If it does, then you know the appliance is getting electrical power.
If your freezer is completely dead, follow these basic troubleshooting steps to restore power:
Check the power cord to make sure that it’s fully plugged into the electrical outlet. Check the power cord for damage and replace the power cord if it’s cut, frayed or damaged.
If the power cord is okay and the freezer is completely dead, reset the house circuit breaker for the freezer outlet.

If the freezer is still dead, test the electrical outlet for power by plugging a nightlight or other small electrical device into the outlet. If the outlet is dead, have an electrician fix the outlet.

If the outlet works and the freezer won’t power up, it may have a defective electronic control board or a bad cold control thermostat. A wiring failure or a number of other failures could also be preventing the freezer from getting power.
If you know the freezer has electrical power, but the compressor won't run, a failed cold control thermostat could be the problem if your freezer has a dial control.
To determine if the freezer cold control thermostat is working,

and check for continuity from the power cord wire that connects to the cold control thermostat and the wire that supplies power to the compressor from the control. If your meter doesn't measure continuity between those wires, then you'll likely need to replace the freezer cold control thermostat because it isn't sending electrical current to the compressor.
Here’s an illustrated guide that shows how to replace the cold control thermostat in a freezer:
How to replace the cold control thermostat in a freezer

When the freezer is getting electrical power but the condenser fan and compressor won’t run because they’re not getting electrical current from the electronic control board, you’ll likely need to replace the circuit board.
Here’s a video that shows how to replace the electronic control board in a freezer:
If you’re uncertain that the electronic control board is bad or you need help resolving your freezer problem, schedule
service and we’ll send a Sears Home Services technician to your home to fix the problem.
What to expect when you experience a Magic Chef freezer not cooling issue
How is the not cooling problem fixed?

Correcting most not cooling problems usually involves replacing the compressor, electronic control board or evaporator. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a freezer that is not cooling

When the freezer is not cooling it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of freezer failures.
What to look out for with a freezer not cooling diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your freezer problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.

full_content.content: Why isn’t my Magic Chef freezer cooling?
The cause could be a faulty thermostat, compressor issue, or blocked airflow. Inspect these components for defects or damage.
How can I fix my Magic Chef freezer if it’s not cooling?
Check the thermostat settings, inspect the compressor, and ensure there are no obstructions blocking airflow.
Could a blocked airflow cause my Magic Chef freezer to stop cooling?
Yes, blocked airflow can prevent proper cooling. Clear any obstructions to allow the airflow to circulate properly.
What should I do if my Magic Chef freezer isn’t cooling?
Check the thermostat, compressor, and airflow. Clean the vents and replace any faulty parts to restore cooling.

full_content.content: How Do Chest Freezers Work?: 2025 Explanation
Learn how chest freezers work and how to troubleshoot common problems.

A freezer bag is a specially designed plastic bag used for the cold storage of food in the freezer, offering protection against freezer burn and preserving the food's freshness and flavor over extended periods.

A freezer compressor is a vital component of a freezer's refrigeration system, functioning as a pump to circulate refrigerant through the system, which cools the interior by absorbing and expelling heat.
What is a Freezer Door Gasket?
A freezer door gasket is a flexible seal that outlines the edge of the freezer door, ensuring an airtight closure to maintain cold temperatures inside and prevent warm air from entering.
What is a Manual Defrost Freezer?
A manual defrost freezer is an appliance that needs to be switched off and allowed to thaw periodically to remove accumulated ice, ensuring efficient operation and storage space maximization.
